column5: I went out again today on Scuzgog, and didnt really have much luck, other than a half decent sized Largemouth. This is the third largemout I have caught this winter, I was just wondering how many other people have caught bass thru the ice this year? I have also heard of a few people catching decent sized muskies thru the ice in a couple different places on the lake. now if I could just find those walleye I would be in business!
Nailed two nice LM though the ice a few years back on Cook's- popping a small spoon I think in about 7 fow for perch.
hooked up with 2 good largies this year but shook them both before gettin them to the hole. seen lots on the camera.
Simcoe + icefishing = smallmouth pretending to be giant perch..
ben on scugog about 12 times..and 8 of those times we had a musky on or at the bottom of one of our holes.. on totaly different parts of the lake.. as well my friend caught a 2lb largie
